From ef6123c134436d0769d2a5a9e997bc2a116906c4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tomaz Zaman <tomaz@mono.si>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 17:55:40 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] ask: XFRM/IPsec hardware offload

Adds the IPsec fast-path offload: a new net/xfrm/ipsec_flow.c/.h pair
wiring xfrm_state into the FMAN SEC (CAAM) engine, plus hook points in
xfrm_input.c/xfrm_output.c/xfrm_policy.c/xfrm_state.c/xfrm_user.c and
the IPv4/IPv6 policy glue (xfrm4_policy.c, xfrm6_policy.c). New Kconfigs
INET_IPSEC_OFFLOAD (net/ipv4/Kconfig) and INET6_IPSEC_OFFLOAD
(net/ipv6/Kconfig), both depending on CPE_FAST_PATH from 010.

Also the CAAM PDB struct packing (drivers/crypto/caam/pdb.h) required
for SEC's view of the IPsec descriptor layout, the net/key/af_key.c
integration, and xfrm.h/netns/xfrm.h additions (xfrm_state.handle/byh,
netns_xfrm.state_byh, xfrm_input_shared) plus pfkeyv2.h UAPI.

Signed-off-by: Tomaz Zaman <tomaz@mono.si>
